						               													<description>Forbidden Psalm is a tabletop skirmish game set in the world of the Mork Bork role playing game. Playable solo, co-operatively or competively, players start by creating their warband of five adventurers, using random tables to add in flaws and features. Weapons and armour are purchased.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The book contains ten scenarios which can be linked together to form a campaign. The game is played out over a 2' by 2' area, using inches to measure movement. Each scenario has a variety of goals to be achieved as enemies are spawned and attack.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Once the scenario has ended -- either due to successfully completing it and escaping, or time running out (it works on a system of rounds), or the warband being wiped out -- experience is determined, treasure and items can be sold for gold, and characters can spend XP to improve their abilities.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game also includes instructions on how to generate scenarios, as well as a bonus cart-racing game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
